title: KINDS OF BLUE Volume 1 (2011) (digital-Empire)
description:
Kinds of Blue - An Anthology of Comics About Depression Vol. 1

What does depression look like? What does depression feel like? When you're stuck in the middle of it, is there anything that actually helps? In this collection of short, original comics, 14 young Australians chronicle their close encounters and experiences with depression, capturing snapshots of what depression is like in order to illuminate what is often unexpressed and help fellow sufferers know they are not alone.

Published by Hive Mindedness Media

Cover by Melanie Boreham
Written by Karen Beilharz, Rebecca Jee, Guangyao Un
Art by Mike Barry, Tim Bywater, Fiona Darwin, Dan Gilmore, Jess Green, Rebecca Jee, Kathleen Jennings, Nancy Malik, Belinda Stead, Jemima Trappel, Paul Wong-Pan

Edited by Karen Beilharz 

Genres: Anthology, Biography, Slice of Life

84 Pages
Digital Release Date: 06/19/2013
Age Rating: 18+ Only
